The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
                A six-year-old boy and an unidentified man were killed in separate mishaps in the city since Tuesday night. Both drivers managed to flee. Yasir Fakir, who lived in a shanty near Armenian Ghat, was playing on Strand Bank Road on Tuesday night, when a speeding Matador knocked him down. He was declared dead at Medical College and Hospital. Early on Wednesday, an unidentified vehicle mowed down a man on CIT Road, in front of ESI Hospital. He was declared dead at RG Kar hospital.    A number of shanties were destroyed in Kundu Lane in Belgachhia when two groups of residents clashed over an eveteasing incident on Wednesday morning. Around 8.15am, 200-odd people blocked the intersection of Belgachhia Road and Kundu Lane for over four hours, demanding the arrest of those who had teased a girl. The protesters allegedly tried to stop passengers from taking the Metro at Belgachhia station.    Sambhu Mahato, 20, a security guard, is feared to have drowned while bathing at Rani Debendrabala Ghat in the North Port police station area on Wednesday morning. The officers of the river traffic police started a search operation but the body could not be traced till late at night.    Tripti Pal, 56, a road sign painter employed by the traffic police, was knocked down by a motorcycle with four riders on Syed Amir Ali Avenue on Wednesday afternoon. Pal was painting white lines on the road. He was taken to Calcutta Port Hospital and admitted to the surgical ward with head and leg injuries. One of the riders was arrested while the other three fled.    Durga Bahadur Sherpa, 52, was found hanging from the ceiling of his room at AJC Bose Road on Wednesday morning. He was taken to Medical College and Hospital, where he was declared dead. Police suspect he committed suicide.    Moumita Sardar, 6, was found floating in a pond near her home at Chandipur in Baruipur on Wednesday. Police said Moumita was missing since Tuesday.    A fire broke out in a pathology laboratory on the first floor of a CMC building on Rowdon Street on Wednesday morning. A tender doused the fire in 30 minutes. No one was injured. The cause of the fire could not be ascertained.            
